# Project Context - Example Template
# Rename to project.yml and customize for your project

## Project Identity
name: your-project-name
description: brief description of what this project does
domain: e.g., e-commerce, healthcare, fintech, devtools

## Technology Stack
language: e.g., typescript, python, go
framework: e.g., react, django, gin
database: e.g., postgres, mongodb, redis
infrastructure: e.g., aws, gcp, kubernetes

## Architecture Patterns
patterns: e.g., repository-pattern, CQRS, event-sourcing
structure: e.g., monolith, microservices, serverless

## Conventions
naming:
  files: e.g., kebab-case, camelCase
  functions: e.g., camelCase, snake_case
  classes: e.g., PascalCase
  constants: e.g., SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE

testing:
  framework: e.g., jest, pytest, go test
  coverage: e.g., minimum 80%
  style: e.g., AAA (arrange-act-assert), BDD

## Commands
# Common commands for this project
build: npm run build
test: npm test
lint: npm run lint
dev: npm run dev

## Key Directories
# Help Claude understand your project structure
src: source code
tests: test files
docs: documentation
scripts: utility scripts

## Domain Terminology
# Project-specific terms Claude should know
# term: definition
# example: "widget" means a dashboard component in this project
